As COVID-19 has shut down the concert industry, fans are having a tough time getting money back for shows that aren't happeningFor weeks, concert fans have endured announcement after announcement of their favorite acts canceling or delaying shows in the wake of the coronavirus pandemic.
There were a couple of reports this week, however, that indicated it will be a long time before concert fans hear — or are a part of — the roar of a crowd again.
Since we're a long way from either of those things happening, refunds for those tickets fans are holding on to should be flowing back into their bank accounts, right?
Fans light up their cellphone flash lights at a sold-out Ed Sheeran concert on September 27, 2017.
No one expected this, but it's wrong to punish fans for purchasing tickets to events.